The paper discusses the development of a domain-specific transformation language for modeling languages, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of graph-based notations and object diagrams, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper's focus on domain-specific languages and their transformation could also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
